cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.SI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies the performance of Non-persistent CSMA/CA protocols in a multi-queue single-server system, which is a common topic in networking research. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the throughput and delay distribution of the proposed system, which involves information transmission and processing. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on the performance analysis of the proposed system, which is a key aspect of performance research. 
4. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper models the system as a queueing system and derives the service time distribution, which is a common approach in systems and control research. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper models multiple access networks as a multi-queue system, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
